description.narrative: Objectives for Ukraine: The goal of the Participant Training Program (PtP) funded by the United States Agency for International Development (USAID) is to advance USAID/Ukraine‚Äôs strategic vision of a stable, democratic, and prosperous Ukraine integrated into Europe. Objectives include: Equip participants with American and European state-of-the-art expertise, progressive models, and new approaches; Introduce participants to the American and European societies to gain understanding of mentality, cultural values, and attitudes; Encourage establishment of professional and cultural links between Ukrainian, American, and European communities; and Facilitate the development of private-government partnerships.

This program supports the Mission's goal for an independent, prosperous, and healthy Ukraine united around core European values in one or more of the following sectors: strengthening of democratic governance, and more inclusive, sustainable, market-driven economic growth.
